
Blade notes:

> helps prevent XSS attacks


{!! !!} <------- stops data from being escaped

{{ <tag> blob </tag>}}  <---- will escape the html stuff


Security:
SQL <---------  pdo methods ->> prepare/bindParam()
html <---------- blade gots us for this
hash passwords <--------- hash(); md5()
validation <------ isset(); empty(); is_interger()/intval()

username limits = /^[a-z0-9_\-]{3, 16}$/
  > "^" = begginig of line
  > "$" = end of line

REGEX!!! for php:
preg_match(regex, string)
  returns TRUE if string matches  regex

preg_replace(regex, replacement,  string)
  returns a new string with all substrings that match regex replaced
  by replacement

preg_split(regex, string)
  returns an array of strings from given string broken apart using the
  given regex as the delimiter (similar to explode but more powerful)































